<article>
  <h1>All Security Articles &amp; Guides</h1>
  <p>Breaking CVE analysis, security tool deep-dives, and practical penetration testing guides. Updated as security news breaks.</p>

  <section style="margin-top: 40px;">
    {% for item in collections.articles %}
    <div class="tool" style="margin-bottom: 32px; padding-bottom: 24px; border-bottom: 1px solid #e9ecef;">
      <h3><a href="{{ item.url }}">{{ item.data.title }}</a></h3>
      <div class="meta">
        <span>Published: {{ item.date | dateString }}</span>
      </div>
      {% if item.data.description %}
      <p>{{ item.data.description }}</p>
      {% endif %}
      <div class="cta">
        <a href="{{ item.url }}" class="button">Read Article →</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% else %}
    <p>No articles published yet. Check back soon.</p>
    {% endfor %}
  </section>

  <section style="margin-top: 48px; background: #f8f9fa; padding: 24px; border-radius: 8px; border-left: 4px solid #667eea;">
    <h2>About This Site</h2>
    <p>BugHunterTools publishes independent security research, CVE analysis, and practitioner guides for bug bounty hunters and penetration testers. Written for technical readers — no hype, real data, honest assessments.</p>
    <p>Content is sourced from SecurityClaw (ClawWorks' AI-assisted security research platform) and independent analysis.</p>
    <p style="margin-top: 12px;"><strong>Also see:</strong> <a href="/demos/">SecurityClaw Live Demos</a> — real tool runs, actual output data.</p>
  </section>

</article>
